        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 8:34PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 834 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Batesburg-Leesville, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Batesburg-Leesville, Red Bank, South Congaree, Gaston, Ridge Spring,
Wagener, Pelion, Gilbert, Summit, Monetta, Perry, Cedar Grove Fire
Station, South Shore Marina, Murray, Thor, Camp Kinard, Hollow Creek
Public Park, Delmar, New Holland, and Samaria Fire Station.

This includes Interstate 20 in South Carolina between mile markers 29
and 54.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
